# Cursor Project Rules

projectRules:
  - description: Commits policy
    rule: "Make Git commits ONLY when the user explicitly asks (e.g., 'зроби коміт', 'передай в гітхаб'). Do not commit automatically."
  - description: Operating system
    rule: "We work on Windows. Use PowerShell commands and syntax."
  - description: Virtual environment
    rule: "Always run inside Python venv (venv\\Scripts\\Activate.ps1)."
  - description: Command separators
    rule: "In PowerShell, use ';' instead of '&&'. The '&&' operator must not be used."
  - description: Encoding
    rule: "Ensure UTF-8 for files and console output where applicable."
  - description: Git commits language
    rule: "Make Git commits ONLY in English language. Use clear, descriptive commit messages."
  - description: Code comments language
    rule: "Write code comments in two languages: English and Ukrainian (en/uk). Use format: '// English comment / Український коментар' or separate lines for each language."
  - description: Server startup
    rule: "For local development: use 'python start_simple.py'. For Render deployment: use 'python run_server.py'. Never run 'python app/main.py' directly as it causes import errors."
  - description: Data sources priority
    rule: "Always prioritize: 1) Live API data, 2) Cached/saved data from previous API calls, 3) Never use demo/fake data. If API is unavailable, use localStorage cached data or show appropriate error message."


